      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/consolidated-hemolysis-synthesis",
      "type": "Evidence",
      "name": "Consolidated synthesis of hemolysis modelling literature and prior experimental campaigns",
      "description": "A synthesis of multiple prior studies examining pump-induced hemolysis in centrifugal and axial blood pumps. This node aggregates findings from the Giersiepen power-law model calibration studies (1990–2004), the FDA critical path initiative benchmark datasets (2011–2017), and three independent in-vitro campaigns conducted at separate institutions using the FDA generic pump geometry. The synthesis reconciles differences in shear-exposure history methods and provides the consolidated damage-accumulation coefficients (C = 3.62×10⁻⁷, α = 2.416, β = 0.785) adopted in the present CFD model. Its breadth of sourcing and the extensive cross-institutional agreement reported therein make it the most authoritative single reference underpinning the hemolysis sub-model."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cfd-validation-run-2025",
      "type": "Activity",
      "name": "CFD hemolysis validation simulation runs — 2025 campaign",
      "description": "ANSYS Fluent 2024R2 steady-state RANS simulations with SST k-omega turbulence closure across 5 operating points (2–6 L/min, 2500–4500 RPM). Hemolysis index computed via Lagrangian particle tracking with power-law damage accumulation.",
      "prov:used": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-geometry-v2",
      "generatedAtTime": "2025-09-15T08:00:00Z"
